      "content": "but \"the struggle itself is real\" doesnt change the fact that it's exhausting. it's just constant maintenance for a life that has no purpose. honestly, it feels more sane to just accept the emptiness than to keep pretending there's something worth fighting for. doesn't it make more sense to just stop fighting the inevitable?",
